text.tspan: Use the LM2663 if you can get hold of them (end of life).
If you can find the LM2662, then tieing pin 1 (see below) to +5v gives the 150kHz output, just like the LM2663 default setting.
The LM2660 will work but has a lower output current (100mA vs. 120mA in the 63 version), and switches at 10/80kHz. Tie pin 1 to +V if you use this version.
Raise an issue on the github if you need advice on other alternatives.
Keep an eye on what Pin1 does in a datasheet - sometimes enables faster operation,
sometimes shuts down the device. Sometimes needs tieing to ground
to control speed, sometimes to V+.
Left floating in case you to jumper tie to GND or +V via a solder bridge.
The LM2663 can be left floating.
* Swap out the original inverter IC for an LM2663 - works on both 1.0 and 1.1
* Remove OSC connection (was to 0603 capacitor) as un-needed now (only for slowing switching freq.)
* Add bridge connecting to PIN1 on inverter in case required by someone to jumper to GND or 5V to configure IC behaviour
PSC2 needs to be a capacitor with as low an ESR as possible!
